{"id":"270593569_Minimax_principle_and_lower_bounds_in_H2-rational_approximation","abstract":"We derive some lower bounds in rational approximation of given degree to\nfunctions in the Hardy space $H^2$ of the disk. We apply these to asymptotic\nerrors rates in approximation to Blaschke products and to Cauchy integrals on\ngeodesic arcs. We also explain how to compute such bounds, either using\nAdamjan-Arov-Krein theory or linearized errors, and we present a couple of\nnumerical experiments on several types of functions. We dwell on the\nAdamjan-Arov-Krein theory and a maximin principle developed in the article \"An\nL^p analog of AAK theory for p \\textgreater{}= 2\", by L. Baratchart and F.\nSeyfert, in the Journal of Functional Analysis, 191 (1), pp. 52-122, 2012.","authors":["Laurent Baratchart","Sylvain Chevillard","Tao Qian"],"meta":["January 2015Journal of Approximation Theory 206","DOI:10.1016/j.jat.2015.03.004","SourcearXiv"],"references":["226985895_Asymptotic_Uniqueness_of_Best_Rational_Approximants_of_Given_Degree_to_Markov_Functions_in_L_2_of_the_Circle","225582700_Graph_Implementations_for_Nonsmooth_Convex_Programs","225075342_Analytic_Properties_of_Schmidt_pairs_for_a_Hankel_operator_and_the_generalized_Schur-Takagi_problem","3423790_Orthonormal_Vector_Fitting_A_Robust_Macromodeling_Tool_for_Rational_Approximation_of_Frequency_Domain_Responses","3324784_Undermodeled_adaptive_filtering_An_a_priori_error_bound_for_the_Steiglitz-McBride_method","3024693_A_technique_for_the_identification_of_linear_systems","3022909_On_the_existence_of_stationary_points_for_the_Steiglitz-McBride_algorithm","2606506_Matrix_Rational_H_2_Approximation_A_Gradient_Algorithm_Based_on_Schur_Analysis","350204825_Espaces_fonctionnels_Utilisation_dans_la_resolution_des_equations_aux_derivees_partielles","323360530_Rational_and_meromorphic_approximation_in_L_P_of_the_circle_system-theoretic_motivations_critical_points_and_error_rates","313173159_Analytic_properties_of_the_Schmidt_pa